“’Ů@7a7d0b3903771460c8c2698e2a1cbb4d19a3d3d2a5c3222bd24883da95f22ab3ÚµTitle: title: Nushell 0.92.1 (hot-fix)
Path: Nushell 0.92.1
Content:




Nushell, or Nu for short, is a new shell that takes a modern, structured approach to your command line. It works seamlessly with the data from your filesystem, operating system, and a growing number of file formats to make it easy to build powerful command line pipelines.
Today, we're releasing version 0.92.1 of Nu, a hotfix release for 0.92.0. This release fixes the following bugs and regressions present in 0.92.0:
The configured hooks should again properly affect the scope (e.g. virtualenv integrations using a hook to activate as an overlay) (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12383] #12383
)
``mkdir``
/
``touch``
 did not correctly resolve relative paths after using 
``cd``
. This is now fixed. (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12394] #12394
)
The default config file created by 0.92.0 assumed that you built with the default feature set including the 
``system-clipboard``
. This is not working on platforms like Android/Termux (termux builds with 
``default-no-clipboard``
). Now we only create keybindings in 
``config.nu``
 that are supported on all platforms and provide suggestions as comments. You may want to recreate 
``config.nu``
 with 0.92.1 if you run into this issue. (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12385] #12385
)
The timing of drop notifications sent to plugins has been corrected. (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12341] #12341
)
::: warning Breaking change

A breaking change to the Rust API of 
``nu-protocol``
 was inadvertently added to the 0.92.1 patch release in PR 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12341] #12341
. Specifically, the method 
``as_mut_any()``
 was added to 
``CustomValue``
, for accessing custom values' data with a mutable reference. This change requires custom value types to implement the method, which breaks API compatibility. Nushell scripts are not affected.

:::
’Ů@2e54dff50e21953803d5b18b57fd4848f978e3532011e81fa02ccb4794e7fd47ÚOTitle: title: Nushell 0.92.1 (hot-fix)
Path: Where to get it
Content:
Nu 0.92.1 is available as 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/releases/tag/0.92.1] pre-built binaries
 or from 
[link: https://crates.io/crates/nu] crates.io
. If you have Rust installed you can install it using 
``cargo install nu``
.
::: tip Note

The optional dataframe functionality is available by 
``cargo install nu --features=dataframe``
.

:::
As part of this release, we also publish a set of optional plugins you can install and use with Nu. To install, use 
``cargo install nu_plugin_<plugin name>``
.
